- 'One-time Solve' refers to a solve type where the process is executed once;
- 'Iterative Solve' refers to a solve type where the process is executed multiple times;
- 'Minimum search proportion' is a measure of the minimum proportion of the search space explored;
- 'CPU time' is the amount of time the CPU spends on executing the solve.

- 'in progress' refers to the status of tasks that are currently being worked on;
- 'Scheduling Project' is a specific project within the database;
- The overall average of variables is calculated across all sub-solves, regardless of their status or project.

- 'Fixed cut type' refers to a specific method of setting a threshold in the algorithm;
- 'Cut value' is a parameter that defines the magnitude of the cut;
- 'Current threshold' is a value that determines the current limit for the algorithm's performance.

sql:
SELECT AVG(cpu_time) AS average_cpu_time
FROM sub_solves
WHERE n > 30 AND p BETWEEN 0.7 AND 0.9;

external_knowledge:
- A "solve" can be a primary process that may have associated sub-processes, referred to as "sub-solves";
- "Blossomed" refers to the growth or expansion of a solve into multiple sub-solves;
- "Search proportion used" is a measure of the extent to which a search algorithm or method was utilized in the solving process.

sql:
